COMPONENT NAME: LKM JMS XML to SQL
AUTHOR: Oracle
DESCRIPTION Loading Knowledge Module Loads XML data from a JMS compliant Message Oriented Middleware (MOM) to any ISO-92 compliant target database. This module uses ODI Agent to read selected XML data from the source MOM and write the result in the target temporary table created dynamically.
REQUIREMENTS The SYNCHRO_JMS_TO_XML option must be set to YES in the first interface loading the message to the XML schema. In order to ensure that the message is successfully recieved AND propagated, the JMS_COMMIT option must be set to NO for all interfaces except the last one.
OPTIONS (Refer to Option descriptions for more information on each option)
LIMITATIONS
Commit the message consumption on the Router (JMS XML)
Load the JMS messages to XML
This option should be set to true for the first interface accessing the message. In subsequent interfaces which access the same message, it should be set to False.
Set this option to false if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Maximum number of messages retrieved [0 .. 4 000 000 000]. 0: All messages are retrieved.

Time to wait in milliseconds for the first message [0 (infinite wait) to 4,000,000,000 (maximum wait)].
If MESSAGETIMEOUT is equal to 0, then there is no timeout.
MESSAGETIMEOUT and MESSAGEMAXNUMBER cannot be both equal to zero.
If MESSAGETIMEOUT=0 and MESSAGEMAXNUMBER=0, then MESSAGETIMEOUT takes the value 1.
Warning!: An interface may retrieve no messages if this timeout value is too small.

Time to wait for each subsequent message in milliseconds [0 (infinite wait) to 4,000,000,000 (maximum wait)]. The default value is 5000.
'''Warning!''': An interface may retrieve only a subset of the messages available in the topic or the queue if this value is too small.
